messages.messageBody:
Milt,
Sorry, no relation to the town or the "ranch." The Water Ranch is in fact a very well designed, new water treatment facility with a series of "natural" ponds heavily planted with native vegetation and managed to provide the right water levels for a variety of species. I was there looking for Streak-backed Oriole which was last recorded in Maricopa county in 1974.

Jim



Jim,

Gilbert Water Ranch, Gilbert, AZ

I can understand the name of the ranch........ but is that town named
after you too ?

Milt
